## Pinjocep — borrower Pro frontend (Next.js)

This rule applies to **`apps/borrower_pro/Pinjocep`**: the **Pinjocep**-branded host app for the TrueKredit Pro borrower experience.

### Shared vs app-local

- Reusable UI, API clients, and utilities live in **`apps/borrower_pro/components/`** and **`apps/borrower_pro/lib/`**. Import with `@borrower_pro/components` and `@borrower_pro/lib` — do not copy shared code into the Pinjocep app.
- Pinjocep-only code belongs here: **`app/`** routes, **`app/components/legal/`** (e.g. `pinjocep-site.ts`), app **`lib/`** (auth handler, re-exports), **`.env`**, and **`docs/planning/`** (e.g. `brand.md`).

### Branding

- **Client name: Pinjocep** — public copy, JSON-LD, and org constants should use Pinjocep (not “Demo Client”, not “Truestack” as a product name).
- Centralise borrower-facing org details in **`app/components/legal/pinjocep-site.ts`** and update in one place when legal or contact data changes.
- **Do not** hardcode hex or one-off colour tokens in pages: follow `docs/planning/brand.md` and theme tokens in `app/globals.css`.

### Technical

- **Auth**: Better Auth client; `BETTER_AUTH_SECRET` and backend URL must match **`backend_pro`**.
- **Ports**: local dev for this app is **3008** (see `package.json` `dev` script); keep `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL` consistent.
